headline: Bitcoin Sets Another Record
summary: Bitcoin notched another record high on Friday, hitting $77,000 for the first time after setting repeated highs earlier in the week. The largest cryptocurrency by market value hit an intraday high of $77,277 before giving back some of its gains.

headline: Factbox-US congressional races where crypto is hoping for big payoffs
summary: The race has not been called yet. Massachusetts Senate: (R) John Deaton vs. (D) Elizabeth Warren (incumbent) The crypto industry spent $4.2 million propping up Massachusetts Senate candidate John Deaton in his race against Senator Elizabeth Warren, who has clashed with digital assets leaders numerous times. Warren, the incumbent, won re-election, Edison Research projects.
